platformd-trustd NEWS
=====================

platformd-trustd (unreleased)

  Audit hardening:

  * Evidence-producing Varlink methods (Attest, GetAttestationToken,
    GetEnrollment, ActivateCredential) are now restricted to root. Producing a
    TPM quote or certification is a signing operation on a shared, slow device;
    reading recorded state stays open to every local peer.
  * The TCG event log is read to EOF rather than truncated at 64 KiB — a
    truncated log cannot be replayed, so a short read now returns no log instead
    of incomplete evidence.
  * A session that already existed when the daemon started is recorded with its
    freshness unknown ("never verified"), not fresh-as-of-now, so a daemon
    restart no longer resets every session's freshness clock. Sessions observed
    being created still start fresh (their creation is a successful auth).
  * pam_platformd.so: the account-phase gate returns PAM_PERM_DENIED (the
    account-phase idiom) rather than PAM_AUTH_ERR; the client accepts either a
    runtime directory ($PLATFORMD_TRUSTD_RUNTIME) or a socket path
    ($PLATFORMD_TRUST_SOCKET).

platformd-trustd 0.1.2

  * pam_platformd.so gains a gate role: with a policy= argument on an auth or
    account line it evaluates a trust policy and passes or fails (fail closed), so
    a PAM stack can offer strong factors only on a verified boot. A verified-boot
    policy is added to EvaluatePolicy. Reference stack in
    pam/platformd-gate.example; documented in pam_platformd(8).

platformd-trustd 0.1.1

  * The kernel-install plugin is installed where kernel-install scans
    (/usr/lib/kernel/install.d, derived from systemd's prefix), so the boot
    reference is provisioned on each UKI update.

platformd-trustd 0.1.0

  * Full RATS Attester and local Verifier: verified-local boot graded against a
    kernel-install-provisioned reference; in-process verification of
    systemd-homed identities (Ed25519); an extend-only NV runtime auth log; a TPM
    quote and an IETF Entity Attestation Token (RFC 9711) bundling boot and
    runtime evidence; attestation-key enrollment by EK credential activation; and
    the fresh-user-verification and local-trusted-session policies. Consumed by
    platformd-secretd.

platformd-trustd 0.0.1

  * Observability core: boot identity and logind sessions as read-only records
    over the Varlink interface io.platformd.Trust; trustctl status /
    list-sessions / session.

  Versioning: the 0.x series is pre-release. The 1.0 tag is gated on an
  independent security review.
